I try not to neutral-vote these days, but I'm neutral-voting this for now.

There is a lot in here to like - particularly the Chicago Spirit section, which managed to steer back from the edge of caricature and keep my interest level high. And the concept of anomalous liquor being linked to Prohibition is a good one.

But for me the structure is working against readability - with three time periods jumbled together between Containment Procedures and Description (quick query, should the 1919 / 1916 dates on the  parts of the collapsibles actually be the same date?), and each of them quite long. It was hard work to keep making the connections between the relevant procedures and description, particularly as the anomaly changes over time. I'm afraid I didn't pick up the explanation for those changes, if it's there.







